I"í<p>249 homes are under threat of demolition by Guinness housing association on the Mansell Street estate in the City of London.</p>

<p>The estate is listed as a â€˜Key Area of Changeâ€™ in the local plan: <a href="https://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/services/environment-and-planning/planning/planning-policy/local-plan/Documents/draft-city-plan-2036.pdf">https://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/services/environment-and-planning/planning/planning-policy/local-plan/Documents/draft-city-plan-2036.pdf</a></p>

<p>In 2016, Guiness submitted a planning application for redevelopment of the estate but this was subsequently withdrawn after protests from residents.</p>

<p>In June 2019, it was <a href="https://www.citymatters.london/mansell-street-estate-residents-must-final-say/">reported</a> that the stalled previous plans were currently being reworked before being presented to residents once again.</p>

